text: Sturgis is a city in Meade County, South Dakota, United States. The population was 7,020 as of the 2020 census. It is the county seat of Meade County. It was founded in 1878. == References == Category:Cities in South Dakota Category:County seats in South Dakota Category:1870s establishments in Dakota Territory Category:1878 establishments in the United States
